PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FAt the heart of the dispute is
OL,7,Fdiffering legal advice over whether a
OL,8,Fone-off payment to striking workers
OL,9,Fcould expose the council to fresh
OL,10,Fequal pay claims.
OL,12,FThat disagreement, more than any
OL,13,Fbreakdown in relations or lack of
OL,14,Fpolitical will, is what continues to
OL,15,Fkeep workers off the streets and bin
OL,16,Fcollections disrupted.
OL,18,FLabour: Negotiations, but within legal
OL,19,Flimits
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FThe Labour-led council insists it
OL,7,Fwants a negotiated settlement. Leader
OL,8,FJohn Cotton confirmed the authority is
OL,9,F"engaged in conversations" with Unite,
OL,10,Fbut declined to discuss the substance
OL,11,Fof those talks.
OL,13,FThe council walked away from formal
OL,14,Fnegotiations last July, arguing it had
OL,15,Freached the limit of what it could
OL,16,Foffer.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@ZO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FIts legal advice suggests that
OL,7,Fagreeing to a one-off payment, a key
OL,8,Fdemand from workers seeking to offset
OL,9,Fwage losses reportedly worth thousands
OL,10,Fof pounds a year, could trigger
OL,11,Ffurther equal pay liabilities.
OL,13,FChanges to the service, including
OL,14,Frestructuring and redundancies, have
OL,15,Falready been implemented.
OL,17,FBut the strike continues, with workers
OL,18,Fholding out for compensation.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FCrucially, Labour has not explained
OL,7,Fhow it could bridge the legal impasse.
OL,8,FWhen asked whether its "red line"
OL,9,Frules out any form of payment, or
OL,10,Fsimply limits its size, Cotton would
OL,11,Fnot be drawn.
OL,13,FThe result is a familiar position: a
OL,14,Fpublic willingness to negotiate, but
OL,15,Fno clear indication of what has
OL,16,Fchanged since talks last collapsed.
OL,18,FReform UK: Review the advice, restart
OL,19,Ftalks
OL,26,@pD@XOUpD@aO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FReform UK says it would "re-establish
OL,7,Fnegotiations effectively and in good
OL,8,Ffaith" and says it has already held
OL,9,Fdiscussions with Unite.
OL,11,FCandidate Jex Parkin argues that its
OL,12,Fcandidates are doctors, nurses and
OL,13,Fbusiness owners with "real world
OL,14,Fexperience" that would strengthen the
OL,15,Fcouncil's negotiating position.
OL,17,FThe party's key proposal is to review
OL,18,Fthe legal advice that currently
OL,19,Funderpins the council's stance.
OL,26,@nD@YOUpD@FO]uD@VOUvD@KO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FBut that raises an obvious question:
OL,7,Fwhat if the review reaches the same
OL,8,Fconclusion?
OL,10,FWithout a clear alternative, Reform's
OL,11,Fapproach appears to hinge on the
OL,12,Fpossibility that different advice
OL,13,Fmight unlock the dispute.
OL,15,FIt offers a change in tone and
OL,16,Fpersonnel, but not necessarily a
OL,17,Fsolution to the underlying risk.
OL,19,FConservatives: Leadership in the room
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FConservative leader Robert Alden
OL,7,Fplaces the emphasis on leadership,
OL,8,Farguing that senior figures must be
OL,9,Fdirectly involved in negotiations.
OL,11,F"If senior people at the top aren't
OL,12,Fwilling to get in the room... it's
OL,13,Fimpossible to set out what is and
OL,14,Fisn't possible," he says.
OL,16,FThe Conservatives acknowledge the
OL,17,Fconstraints, saying the council cannot
OL,18,Fsimply concede to union demands if
OL,19,Fdoing so would breach equal pay law.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@PO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FBut, like others, they argue that
OL,7,Fwithout direct engagement, a legally
OL,8,Fsound compromise will never be found.
OL,10,FYet again, the missing piece is what
OL,11,Fthat compromise might look like in
OL,12,Fpractice.
OL,14,FLiberal Democrats: Negotiate now,
OL,15,Frestructure later
OL,17,FThe Liberal Democrats echo the call to
OL,18,F"work through the differences" between
OL,19,Fthe two sides, particularly around
OL,20,Ftheir conflicting legal
OL,21,Finterpretations.
OL,26,@zD@AOUzD@^O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FIn the longer term, they suggest a
OL,7,Fmore structural solution. This would
OL,8,Finvolve splitting waste services into
OL,9,Fmultiple contracts and outsourcing
OL,10,Fthem, shifting equal pay risks onto
OL,11,Fprivate providers.
OL,13,FThat may offer a future model, but it
OL,14,Fdoes little to resolve the immediate
OL,15,Fdispute.
OL,17,FThe same legal disagreement would
OL,18,Fstill need to be confronted in the
OL,19,Fshort term.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FGreens: Return to talks, rethink the
OL,7,Fadvice
OL,9,FThe Greens are among the most critical
OL,10,Fof the council's approach, arguing it
OL,11,Fhas been "negligent" in allowing
OL,12,Fnegotiations to stall since last
OL,13,Fsummer.
OL,15,FWhen pressed on the council's legal
OL,16,Fposition, they point to Unite's
OL,17,Fopposing advice, suggesting the
OL,18,Fauthority under them might give
OL,19,Fgreater weight to the union's case.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37212
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,F"We need to listen to the other side
OL,7,Fmore," says candidate Julien Pritchard.
OL,9,FThat raises a key question. Would a
OL,10,FGreen-led council be prepared to set
OL,11,Faside its own legal advice in favour
OL,12,Fof the union's interpretation? And if
OL,13,Fso, how would it manage the potential
OL,14,Ffinancial risks?
OL,16,FAs with the other parties, the
OL,17,Femphasis is on process rather than a
OL,18,Fdefined endgame.
OL,20,FA stalemate no one has cracked
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@FO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G12/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37213
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776863483
OL,3,CBin strike: plenty of promises, but no
OL,4,Cparty has a clear way out
OL,6,FBeyond calls for talks to resume,
OL,7,Fanswers remain vague.
OL,9,FAt its core, this is a legal dispute
OL,10,Fover what is permissible and what
OL,11,Fcould cost the council millions. Until
OL,12,Fthat is resolved, negotiations risk
OL,13,Frepeating the same arguments.
OL,15,FSome may be holding back a plan, but
OL,16,Fthere is little sign of it.
OL,18,FA change in leadership alone is
OL,19,Funlikely to end the strike.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G13/14
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
